title: Farewell to you my 2nd Graders
author: brenda
text: farewell to each one of you as you move on ahead  remember your spelling and the books that you read.  hold on to the memories we formed in second grade remember the laughter and the friends that you made.   remember when reading seemed an impossible task when vowels were just five letters pulled from the mass a couple of consonants thrown in for good measure formed a word that made sense and became a great treasure!  remember the bat that hung from the eaves in the fall,  remember our gerbil rolling around in her ball.  while counting our coins and learning each name mrs.  phillips and mrs.  knutsen got ready for fame.   we learned to sit quiet and to limit the wiggles except when miguel said something to make us all giggle.  we can count on the value of money to remain the same and learned to be truthful and accept the blame.   telling time was quite easy as long as you found that one hand tells minutes and one hand tells hour.  our daily calendar provided a time to chart teeth and autumn inspired a wall of bright wreaths.   estimating items each week in a jar enlightened the meaning of a sky full of stars.  sharing each friday was cherished by all  a variety of items from a mite to a doll.   our feet learned the polka with minimal effort andea's african adventure enriched our reports.  the wizard of oz took main stage in our class our stepping stones built from rocks and from glass.   magic treehouse swept us away to new lands our geoboards donned with a stretch of a band paper mache was a long drawn out task will i do it again?!!!. . please don't ask!  each one of you hold a special place in my heart may you remember our year as you begin a new start.  as i bid you farewell a
